name: ExtensionProvenance_Entity
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.Provenance.entity` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `Provenance.entity` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `Provenance.entity` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`Provenance.entity` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `Provenance.entity` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `Provenance.entity` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `Provenance.entity` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `Provenance.entity` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `Provenance.entity`, but has no comparisons.

element.short: Entity is attributed to this agent
element.definition: The entity is attributed to an agent to express the agent's responsibility for that entity, possibly along with other agents. This description can be understood as shorthand for saying that the agent was responsible for the activity which used the entity.
element.comment: A usecase where one Provenance.entity.agent is used where the Entity that was used in the creation/updating of the Target, is not in the context of the same custodianship as the Target, and thus the meaning of Provenance.entity.agent is to say that the entity referenced is managed elsewhere and that this Agent provided access to it.  This would be similar to where the Entity being referenced is managed outside FHIR, such as through HL7 V2, v3, or XDS. This might be where the Entity being referenced is managed in another FHIR resource server. Thus it explains the Provenance of that Entity's use in the context of this Provenance activity.
